HEADWORD: Orbitelae
<hw>Or`bi*te"lae</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
L. <ets>orbis</ets> an orb + <ets>tela</ets> a web.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of spiders, including those that make
geometrical webs, as the garden spider, or Epeira.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

